List<TA1ChangeHandler.FieldChange> changes =
    TA1ChangeHandler.handleTrackedChange(
        blobServiceClient,
        trackedDataContainerClient,     // "tracked-data"
        "CustomerContainer",            // logical Cosmos container
        docId,
        newDoc,
        trackedFields,
        context.getLogger());

Notes
	•	Uses downloadStream and upload(BinaryData, overwrite=true) (non‑deprecated).
	•	Uses findBlobsByTags to locate the current latest.
	•	ETag guard on demote step, with configurable retries/backoff via env:
	•	TA1_MAX_RETRIES (default 4)
	•	TA1_BACKOFF_MS (default 200)
	•	First‑time logic:
	•	If no latest is found but {docId}.json baseline exists:
	•	If no tracked differences: tag the baseline as latest=true.
	•	If differences: write a new timestamped version and promote it.
	•	If baseline doesn’t exist: write first version and promote it.

